  "source": "Theorem:\n. \"Theorem 4.22 (Zorn's Lemma)\"\ngiven:\n. X is \\set\nwhere:\n. \\partially.ordered{X}\n. not:\n  . X = \\empty.set\n. forAll: A is \\set\n  where:\n  . A \\.chain.in./ X\n  then:\n  . exists: u is \\set\n    suchThat:\n    . allOf:\n      . u \"in\" X\n      . u \\.upper.bound.of./ A\nthen:\n. exists: m is \\set\n  suchThat:\n  . m \\.maximal.in./ X\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Suppose $X$ is a non-empty partially ordered set such that every chain in $X$ has an upper bound in $X$. Then $X$ contains a maximal element. Zorn's lemma is the first of the two major statements shown to be equivalent to the axiom of choice.\"\nId: \"7395d1bd-f430-4b75-a515-9b992034553c\"",
